<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-42-1125 </DOCNO><TEXT>Detailed recommendations by the Environment Committee to the UK Governmenton air pollution are summarized under the main headings of Acid Rain,Lead in Petrol, Chlorofluorocarbons and the Ozone Layer, and the GreenhouseEffect. These are then dealt with in greater detail against the backgroundof evidence received by the Committee, the minutes of which appear atthe end of the report. Appendices include two earlier reports from theCommittee on acid ran and the Government's reply to the first of these.(U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>